The MHPCO Claim Office kata is complete. Here's a summary:

**44 tests passing** covering the full specification:
- Quote edge cases (empty list, unknown types)
- Single item base premiums (sword, amulet, staff, potion)
- Component pricing (individual + block of 3 alike)
- Item-specific modifiers (cursed surcharge, high enchantment)
- Policy-wide modifiers (loyalty, first insurance, follow-up)
- Rounding (premiums up, payouts down)
- Integration examples (newcomer, long-standing customer)
- Claim reimbursement (standard, high enchantment, dragon material)
- Deductible per damage event
- Multiple items of same type
- Cap exhaustion across successive claims
- Claim edge cases (invalid items, negative damage)

**Files created:**
- `src/claim-office.ts` — core business logic with `claimOffice` function
- `src/claim-office.spec.ts` — 44 tests
- `src/cli.ts` — CLI entry point (reads JSON from stdin, writes to stdout)
- `experiment-done.txt` — completion marker
